StartPoint: Take Hwy 89 through Lassen Park to the boat launch to the Manzanita Lake trail.
Directions: Take Hwy 89 through the Entrance Station at Manzanita Lake.  Before the campground and store, take a right turn into the boat launch area.  Park here.  At the end of the road (where the circle round is) you will find the Manzanita Lake Trail.  (You can also access this trail from the back of the first campground loop.)  Walk the trail until you come to the junction of the trail coming from the campground.  At this junction there is a sign posted, "No Bicylces on trail".  From this point, walk approx. 270m to the reference PIJE (tagged #95, DBH-70cm).  From this tree, the plot center is 150m at 230 degrees.  (Only the origin and he Brown's are tagged at this time.)
Comments: Adjacent the decadent shrubby area where the plot is located is an area that has been burned by wildfire.  This areas is becoming badly infested with thistle.  This will likely be a problem after the Stonehenge RX burn.

StartPoint: Highway 89 (the road through the park) to Manzanita Lake boat launch to Manzanita Lake Trail.
Directions: Take Hwy 89 into the park via the Entrance Station at Manzanita Lake.  Before you come to the campground store, take a right into the boat launch area.  Park here.  At the back end of the parking area (where the road circles back around) you will find the Manzanita Lake Trail.  Take this trail.  When you come to the junction of the trail coming from the campground (a sign is there stating, "No Bicycles on Trail"), walk another 475m to a reference tree (forked PIJE tagged #472 on the side facing away from the lake, DBH-112cm).  At this tree, leave the trail walking on the SE side of the drainage approx. 357m at 240 degrees.  Where this drainage joins another small drainage from the east you will find a reference stake.  From this stake climb uphill 100m at 180 degrees to the lot center.    Note: Distance and bearing as the crow flies from the reference tree to the plot is 413m at 230 degrees.  Not the most freindly way to walk though!!!
Comments: This plot is a combination fire effects plot and fuels plot.  We collected all the regular fuels plot data and added a veg transect and shrub belt, as well as tagging trees in to 100'x100' plots.  See trip report for more detailed info.

StartPoint: Take Hwy 89 (in the park) to Manzanita Lake Campground.
Directions: Drive into the campground and park at the back end of Loop B.  At Campsite B29 there are a set of bear-proof recycling and garbage cans (this is probably the best parking spot).  From those cans there is a reference tree 95m away @ 263 degrees.  This is an ABCO, DBH 76cm, tagged #99 on the side facing away from the campground.  From this tree the plot is 530m away @ 240 degrees.
Comments: This plot is a LAVO fules plot that we added some FMH protocols to.  See Metadata and FMH-7 and the narrative of protocols for more information.
